.\" heirloom-port-snapshot(7)
.TH HEIRLOOM-PORT-SNAPSHOT 7 "2026-07-02" "Heirloom Darwin port" "Port ALM"
.SH NAME
heirloom-port-snapshot \- git-tag the current state as a release snapshot
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B make snapshot
.SH DESCRIPTION
Creates an annotated git tag of the form
.B snapshot-YYYYMMDD-HHMMSSZ
pointing at the current HEAD. Refuses if the working tree is dirty
(commit or stash first).
.PP
Snapshot tags are automation-friendly release markers. Push them
individually with
.B git push origin <tag>
or all at once with
.BR "git push --tags" .
.SH USE CASES
.RS 4
.IP \(bu 2
Before running
.B make test-manual
to have a reproducible "before" reference.
.IP \(bu 2
Before applying an experimental patch series.
.IP \(bu 2
As a lightweight release marker when semantic-version tagging is
not yet warranted.
.RE
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Tag created.
.TP
.B 1
Working tree is dirty; tag not created.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR git-tag (1),
.BR heirloom-port-lifecycle (7)
